1957: Klebsiella quasipneumoniae subsp. quasipneumoniae M17277
Identifiers: BioSample: SAMN10340875; Sample name: Klebsiella quasipneumoniae subsp. quasipneumoniae M17277
Organism: Klebsiella quasipneumoniae subsp. quasipneumoniae
Attributes:
    /strain="M17277"
    /collected by="Dr. Ricardo Gutierrez, Hospital de Ninos"
    /collection date="2014"
    /geographic location="Argentina"
    /host="Homo sapiens"
    /host disease="Erythrodermic psoriasis"
    /isolation source="rectal swab"
    /latitude and longitude="34.594590 S 58.411377 W"
    /sub species="quasipneumoniae"
Description:
Klebsiella quasipneumoniae subsp. quasipneumoniae M17277 was isolated from a rectal swab of a paediatric patient suffering from erythrodermic psoriasis. M17277 harboured blaNDM-1 in a type 1 IncC plasmid and plasmid-mediated quinolone resistance genes.
Accession: SAMN10340875	ID: 10340875
